summary: An ordinance authorizing and directing the City Comptroller to advertise for sale negotiable bonds of the City of Seattle in the sum of $500,000.00, being half of the $1,000,000.00 voted at the special election held in the City of Seattle on the 29th day of December, 1908, under and by virtue of Ordinance No. 19606, approved November 27, 1908.
